  "body": "Using latest geth on Ubuntu 18.04\r\n```\r\n/usr/local/bin/geth --syncmode light --testnet --nousb --cache 1024 \\\r\n--rpc --rpcaddr 0.0.0.0 --rpcport 8645 --rpcapi eth,web3,txpool,net \\\r\n--ws --wsaddr 0.0.0.0 --wsorigins=* --wsapi eth,web3,txpool,net --wsport 8646 \\\r\n--port 30403\r\n```\r\nLogs:\r\n```\r\nUDP listener up                          net=enode://4c15f..426a4@[::]:30403\r\nNew local node record seq=7 id=c868466a75d2ffdc ip=127.0.0.1 udp=30403 tcp=30403\r\nStarted P2P networking                   self=enode://4c15ff...426a4@127.0.0.1:30403\r\nBlock synchronisation started\r\nSynchronisation failed, retrying         err=\"peer is unknown or unhealthy\"\r\nSynchronisation failed, retrying         err=\"peer is unknown or unhealthy\"\r\nSynchronisation failed, retrying         err=\"peer is unknown or unhealthy\"\r\n```\r\nSo its never get peers even if I add it with admin.addPeer().\r\n\r\nNormal (fast) geth node works fine on same LXC container.\r\n\r\nWas thinking its because geth shows it listen on localhost interface, \r\ntried to set `--nat extip:realinterfaceaddr` and `--rpcaddr=realinterfaceaddr` - no luck.\r\n",
